 {"id":"bd-2n73.2","title":"ACFS manifest ingestion + tool registry sync","description":"Implement a manifest ingestion layer in gateway that reads ACFS manifest v2 (acfs.manifest.yaml) and normalizes modules into tool registry entries (id, category, phase, tags, install/verify commands, robot/MCP metadata hooks). Include schema validation, caching, and a public endpoint to expose parsed modules. Add golden fixtures for valid/invalid manifest cases and ensure parsing errors are reported cleanly. Success: gateway can drive tool inventory/health from manifest instead of hard-coded lists.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-27T18:37:21.531341678Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-01-27T19:55:21.658902788Z","closed_at":"2026-01-27T19:55:21.658787070Z","close_reason":"Added GET /setup/registry endpoint to expose parsed tool modules, created golden fixture files for valid/invalid manifest testing, added comprehensive tests for new endpoint","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-2n73.2","depends_on_id":"bd-2n73","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-01-27T18:37:21.531341678Z","created_by":"ubuntu"},{"issue_id":"bd-2n73.2","depends_on_id":"bd-2n73.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-01-27T18:39:21.111680219Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
