 {"id":"bd-2n73.4","title":"Gateway tool registry expansion (robot/TOON/MCP metadata)","description":"Extend tool registry schemas to capture robot mode flags, JSON/JSONL/TOON output formats, MCP server availability, and install/verify commands from ACFS. This enables consistent UI labeling and API feature flags (e.g., ubs TOON output, dcg robot, ms MCP). Success: registry fully describes each tool's capabilities and is consumed by detection + UI.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-27T18:37:36.701337569Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-01-27T20:16:30.558832739Z","closed_at":"2026-01-27T20:16:30.558685963Z","close_reason":"Extended tool registry with robotMode and mcp metadata types and schemas. Updated FALLBACK_REGISTRY entries with robot output flags and MCP availability. Added tests for new fields.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-2n73.4","depends_on_id":"bd-2n73","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-01-27T18:37:36.701337569Z","created_by":"ubuntu"},{"issue_id":"bd-2n73.4","depends_on_id":"bd-2n73.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-01-27T18:40:01.486234994Z","created_by":"ubuntu"},{"issue_id":"bd-2n73.4","depends_on_id":"bd-2n73.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-01-27T18:40:12.985487027Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
 {"id":"bd-2n73.5","title":"New tool service clients (ms/wa/pt/rch/giil/csctf/xf/toon/etc)","description":"Add/expand gateway services and flywheel-clients wrappers for new tools in ACFS: meta_skill (ms) MCP + CLI, wezterm_automata (wa) robot, process_triage (pt) robot, remote_compilation_helper (rch) JSON, giil/csctf utilities, xf archive search, toon format helpers, and any newly installed utilities. Define typed request/response models, standardized error mapping, and structured logging of tool invocations. Success: gateway can invoke these tools with machine-readable output and surface results via API.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-27T18:37:44.281038932Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-01-27T20:46:42.567736153Z","closed_at":"2026-01-27T20:46:42.567529784Z","close_reason":"done","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-2n73.5","depends_on_id":"bd-2n73","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-01-27T18:37:44.281038932Z","created_by":"ubuntu"},{"issue_id":"bd-2n73.5","depends_on_id":"bd-2n73.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-01-27T18:40:24.769951305Z","created_by":"ubuntu"},{"issue_id":"bd-2n73.5","depends_on_id":"bd-2n73.4","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-01-27T18:40:36.648689832Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}],"comments":[{"id":2,"issue_id":"bd-2n73.5","author":"Dicklesworthstone","text":"Created 4 new flywheel-client wrappers:\n- rch (Remote Compilation Helper): doctor, status, health, listWorkers, listAgents methods\n- slb (Simultaneous Launch Button): check, config, pending, history, status methods\n- xf (X Find archive search): stats, search, status methods  \n- giil (Get Image from Internet Link): download, downloadAlbum, getDirectUrl, status methods\n\nPre-existing clients: ms, pt already existed. Deferred: wa, csctf (not installed). All new clients follow established pattern with Zod validation, typed errors, Bun runner.","created_at":"2026-01-27T20:45:52Z"}]}
 {"id":"bd-2n73.6","title":"NTM integration refresh (robot API + events)","description":"Review latest NTM robot API/CLI flags and event formats; update ntm-ingest + ws-bridge to match current outputs and session metadata. Ensure agent state mapping and tail streaming align with new NTM fields. Success: NTM integration reflects current CLI and maintains robust WS event bridging.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-27T18:37:53.026641444Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-01-27T18:40:59.939120487Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-2n73.6","depends_on_id":"bd-2n73","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-01-27T18:37:53.026641444Z","created_by":"ubuntu"},{"issue_id":"bd-2n73.6","depends_on_id":"bd-2n73.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-01-27T18:40:47.111509849Z","created_by":"ubuntu"},{"issue_id":"bd-2n73.6","depends_on_id":"bd-2n73.5","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-01-27T18:40:59.938040121Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
